Description
===========

CoStLy is a free library of complex interval standard functions. 


Installation
============

1) Make sure you have
	a) the GNU C++ compiler gcc 2.95.2 and
	b) the filib++ library (version 2.0)
   installed.

2) Unpack the sources with the command "tar -xvzf CoStLy-0.1.tgz".
   This unpacks the CoStLy files in the current directory.


Notice on point 1)
==================

You can download the filib++ package from

http://www.math.uni-wuppertal.de/org/WRST/software/filib++/filib++.distribution.tar.gz

To install the library see the README file.


Technical support
=================

None. CoStLy is free software, remember?

In case of trouble, you may try sending an email to one of the above adresses,
with fingers crossed for reply.
